      APIdocs
    </h1>

    <p>
      The <a href="doc/index.html">APIdocs</a> provides a comprehensive interface with access
      package documents, such as the README and Release Notes as well as convenient access to
      both the Core and More RDoc APIs.
    </p>

  </div>

  <div class="section">

    <h1>
      <a class="big" href="quick/index.html">
        <img src="img/appleslice.jpg" width="60px;" align="absmiddle"/>
      </a>
      Sidebar
    </h1>

    <p>
      <a class="big"
         href="javascript: window.open('http://facets.rubyforge.org/quick/index.html', 'facets_quickdocs',
               config='height=470, width=551, toolbar=no, menubar=no, scrollbars=no, status=0,
               resizable=no, location=no, directories=no'); void(0);">
        <img src="img/mini.png" align="right" style="margin: -15px 3px;"/>
      </a>

      The <a href="quick/index.html">Sidebar</a> provides a convenient "quick reference" interface
      to the RDoc API documentation. It is especailly useful for browsers that support sidebar pages,
      such as Firefox. Simply drag-and-drop the "apple slice image" (left of this text) to a toolbar,
      then alter it's properties to open as a <i>sidebar</i>. If your browser doesn't support sidebars,
      or if you simply prefer, you can use the
      <a href="javascript: window.open('http://facets.rubyforge.org/quick/index.html', 'facets_quickdocs',
               config='height=470, width=551, toolbar=no, menubar=no, scrollbars=no, status=0,
               resizable=no, location=no, directories=no'); void(0);">Mini API</a> instead.
      This offers the same interface, but in a small stand-alone window.
    </p>

  </div>

